  "prompt": "Where do earthquakes mostly happen?",
  "response": "Earthquakes mostly happen along tectonic plate boundaries due to the movement and interaction of these plates. The most seismically active regions include:\n\n1. **Pacific Ring of Fire**: This area encircles the Pacific Ocean and hosts numerous earthquakes and volcanic eruptions. It includes places like Japan, Indonesia, New Zealand, the west coast of North and South America (California, Chile, etc.).\n\n2. **Himalayan Region**: This area experiences significant seismic activity due to the collision between the Indian Plate and the Eurasian Plate.\n\n3. **Mediterranean-Asian Seismic Belt**: Extending from the Mediterranean region through Asia, this belt includes countries like Turkey, Greece, Iran, and Italy.\n\n4. **Mid-Atlantic Ridge**: This underwater mountain range in the Atlantic Ocean is a divergent boundary where earthquakes occur due to the plates moving apart.\n\n5. **San Andreas Fault**: Located in California, USA, this transform fault is well-known for its earthquake activity.\n\nThese regions are prone to frequent earthquakes due to the constant movement of the Earth's lithosphere.",
